//menu.dic
/*This file is, as per the name, for the main chat menu that appears upon double-clicking.
There should be minimal dialogue here, but there's many one-offs that I have to account for
here. Personal menu for right-click is NOT INCLUDED HERE!*/

//To-do: If you can change the menu to run from text arrays in the updates file, updating the menu is free.
//We could just put the menu builder in the update file...but what to do about OpenSakuraMenu?

/*I need to acknowledge the elusive 'lastTalk' variable here. I assumed it was written by a professional, since
it was in camelcase. I also assumed that pro accounted for it in SSP. It appears that was merely an illusion.
lastTalk was actually made by presumably the second-gen author, and isn't tracked by SSP. It was only called in
AITalk. If you want it to repeat dialogue said in menus, you have to do  it manually.*/

/*OpenSakuraMenu calls the MenuRun function to DISPLAY the actual menu.  Since it's calling the MenuRun function itself, 
it keeps any pre-menu dialogue from cluttering the actual menu display function. If you don't want dialogue with the menu,
then you can just call MenuRun wherever you want and not have to deal with this.
Beautiful.
For those of you with no prior coding experience, it's possible to create multiple menus.
This is what SickMenuRun does--it's a completely different menu.*/
OpenSakuraMenu
{
	//This if/else block sifts through all the custom stuff I added.
	//Because they have different priority levels I can't enforce,
	//we check Curr_Event first since it's highest priority.
	if Curr_Event == "sickbob"
	{
		"\0\s[15]..."
		--
		//Here's the SickMenu I was bragging about. Simple. Easy.
		SickMenuRun
	}
	//If Bob's upset, you can't interact, so we just don't call the menu.
	elseif mood == "Upset"
	{
		//IS THIS EVER USED?? CHECK!!
		"\0\s[14]\b2I'm sorry, %(username). \w8I just don't feel like talking.\e"
		//change balloon and add an array here
	}
	else
	{	
		//Checks things like items and interaction stats 
		if cookie == 1
		{
			"\0\s[13]\b2Do you have any more cookies?"
			--
			MenuRun
		}		
		//If you've talked a lot and tally it, mention here
		
		//Normal opening dialogue
		"\0\s[0]\b2Hi, %(username)!"
		"\0\s[0]\b2Oh, hi, %(nickname)!"
		//We only need 5-6 of these, so do we need an array?
		//No. It's too overkill for basic stuff.
		--
		MenuRun
	}
}

/*Behold, my beautiful menu generation function...composed of if/else's.*/
MenuRun
{	
	//Get time/date for display
 	wd = GetWeekDay
 	ap = GetAP
 	nowmin = Getnowmin
 	nowhour = Getnowhour
	--
	"\n\n\_q\b2" //quick session makes it all appear instantly
	--
	//If lastTalk's been set/tracked, you can ask to see it in the menu.
	if lastTalk != ""
	{
	  "\![*]\q[Repeat Last Dialogue,OnLastTalk]\n\n[half]"
	  "\![*]\q[Could you repeat that?,OnLastTalk]\n\n[half]"
	  //"\![*]\q[What did you say?,OnLastTalk]\n\n[half]"
	 }
	--
	//Runs AITalk.
 	"\![*]\q[Say something,OnAITalk]\n"
	//"\![*]\q[Talk to me,OnAItalk]\n"
	//Despite being able to write multiple menu dialogue options 
	//everywhere else, you can't do it for AITalk for some dumb reason...
	--
	//If a current event is occurring (NOT GUARANTEED ON RUNTIME), allows
	//user to talk about it, otherwise don't display.
	if Curr_Event != ""
	{
	"\![*]\q[What's happening lately?,event]\n"
	}
	--
	//Item option.
	"\![*]\q[Items & Interaction,itemselect]\n"
	--
	//Hobbies option.
	"\![*]\q[Ask about hobbies,OnHobbyMenuDisp]\n"
	--
	//A new line break wasn't enough, so I put in a spacer too.
	"...\n"
	--
	//These are self-explanatory--I did minimal work here; they weren't important to me.
	//DON'T COMMENT IN THE MIDDLE OF THESE; THEY'RE IN A QUOTE!
	"\![*]\q[Metadata,OnMTDataPull_Comprehensive]\n/
	\![*]\q[Settings & Configuration,configuration]\n/ 
	\![*]\q[SSP Bonus Functions,dosomething]\n\n[half]/
 	\![*]\q[Cancel,CANCEL]\n\n\n[half]%(wd) %(nowhour):%(nowmin) %(ap), %(month)/%(day)/%(year)\e" 
	//Do I want to use all those? Decide later. Delete Metadata for public release.
}

/*I'm entertaining the thought of making all the menus arrays like the character ask one, but since there are so many if's,
I'm not sure if it will work properly. Plus, seeing that I only have two main menus as of now, there's not really a reason 
to do so now...but I'll leave this here for my own reference in the future.

UPDATE: Theoretically this could be more efficient for the sick menu, depending on how you structure it with your if's.*/
Menu_Array_MAINMENU : array
{
	//function is below!
	//multiple reponses should work in brackets; if-else as well?
	"What's happening lately?.event"
	"Configuration Menu.configuration"
	"Items & Interaction.itemselect"
	"Ask About Hobbies.OnHobbyMenuDisp"
	"Metadata.OnMTDataPull_Comprehensive"
	"Functions.dosomething"
}

